1. To build my project using "make":

>>$ make clean
>>$ make

2. This "make" command generates three files run-mapreduce, mapreduce.o, usr_functions.o and main.o

3. To run the program for "counter" functionality:

>>$ ./run-mapreduce counter ./input-moon10.txt 4 

4. To run the program for "finder" functionality:

>>$ ./run-mapreduce finder ./input-moon10.txt 4 "Lord"

5. I have implemented all the requirements as described inside the project.

6. My project works for all the scenarios and test cases as descripbed inside the project description:
   TEST CASES:
   (a) ./run-mapreduce counter ./input-moon10.txt 4
   (b) ./run-mapreduce counter ./input-alice30.txt 6 
   (c) ./run-mapreduce counter ./input-warpeace.txt 5 
   (d) ./run-mapreduce finder ./input-moon10.txt 4 "Lord"
   (e) ./run-mapreduce finder ./input-alice30.txt 2 "Rabbit"
   (f) ./run-mapreduce finder ./input-warpeace.txt 4 "Peace"

7. Output of my program for the above mentioned test cases:

